{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, PCFG-surprisals, while effective, may be limited by the constraints of their grammatical frameworks and less extensive training data.",
    "The stronger correlations observed with LLM-based surprisal indices highlight their potential for advancing L2 assessment.",
    "These indices can provide more detailed feedback on learners' proficiency, particularly in complex linguistic constructs such as degree expressions.",
    "Our results provide an approach to reveal L2 learners' interlanguage system's development in degree expressions.",
    "L2 teachers and researchers may benefit from specifying and personalizing the design in teaching materials, based on learners L1 and proficiency levels."
  ]
}